00:17.734 --> 00:19.168
What time is it?

00:21.087 --> 00:23.956
Late.

00:24.040 --> 00:25.907
Something happened.

00:25.959 --> 00:27.209
Not good, Tony.

00:27.260 --> 00:30.412
What? What's
going on, Jimmy?

00:30.463 --> 00:32.747
After the fight,
Ryan was bad.

00:32.799 --> 00:35.134
Ryan? What about Ryan?

00:35.218 --> 00:37.386
He felt sick, Tony.

00:37.437 --> 00:39.555
So I took him
to the hospital, you know?

00:39.606 --> 00:41.890
People, they started
screaming at me.

00:41.941 --> 00:45.144
They started yelling
at <i>me,</i> Tony.

00:45.228 --> 00:46.979
About Ryan?
Are they doing tests?

00:47.063 --> 00:48.864
Yeah, I think so.

00:48.931 --> 00:50.983
But, see, when I went outside,

00:51.067 --> 00:55.537
the, uh, screaming,
it didn't stop.

00:55.605 --> 00:56.655
Who was screaming?

00:56.740 --> 00:59.491
These crazy guys, man.
They were crazy.

00:59.576 --> 01:02.728
And I told them to leave me alone
and they wouldn't listen.

01:02.796 --> 01:04.129
They just wouldn't listen.

01:04.214 --> 01:06.281
And then I saw
all sorts of stuff.

01:06.332 --> 01:07.966
Stuff?
What kind of stuff?

01:08.051 --> 01:10.052
Like I saw my ma,

01:10.119 --> 01:12.805
then I saw my old man.

01:12.889 --> 01:15.557
And then...

01:15.625 --> 01:18.594
And then I saw
the dude at the fight.

01:18.645 --> 01:20.429
But when I looked up,

01:20.480 --> 01:23.298
you see, the lights,
they started spinning.

01:23.349 --> 01:25.794
Tony, it was like--
it was like God was

01:25.819 --> 01:26.968
reaching his hand down

01:26.969 --> 01:29.321
and he was trying
to take Ryan.

01:29.406 --> 01:31.106
Look, look, Jimmy,

01:31.157 --> 01:32.825
you're punchy, J.,
you know?

01:32.909 --> 01:34.610
Ryan's gonna be fine.

01:34.661 --> 01:36.829
You had a tough fight
tonight.

01:36.913 --> 01:38.497
You gotta sleep it off.

01:38.581 --> 01:40.115
You sure?

01:40.166 --> 01:42.534
In the morning
everything will be ok.

01:46.089 --> 01:48.340
Yeah, you're probably right.

01:48.425 --> 01:50.992
I'm gonna be fine.
Everything's gonna be fine.

01:51.044 --> 01:52.845
Thanks, Tony.

01:52.929 --> 01:54.213
All right.

02:29.382 --> 02:32.167
Jeez, I hope you're
training for something.

02:32.218 --> 02:35.003
Or are you just
doing sprints for fun?

02:35.054 --> 02:37.005
No, I'm, uh...

02:37.056 --> 02:40.008
I'm trying to do this
triathlon in February, so...

02:40.059 --> 02:42.544
Oh, yeah. The FBI one.
You're an agent.

02:42.595 --> 02:45.264
Yeah, it is the FBI one.

02:45.348 --> 02:47.048
I'm not supposed to ask
if you're an agent.

02:47.100 --> 02:49.551
I work for
the Justice Department.

02:49.602 --> 02:51.019
- Oh.
- Yeah.

02:51.070 --> 02:53.856
I've seen you doing laps
at the Y, too.

02:53.907 --> 02:56.692
And you're training
for surveillance?

02:56.743 --> 02:58.694
I am doing
an MS triathlon.

02:58.745 --> 03:02.614
It's in January, but I'm not in
as big a rush as you.

03:02.699 --> 03:04.783
Well, I just have
about 45 minutes a day,

03:04.868 --> 03:08.787
so, you know, between
work and home and--it's hard.

03:08.855 --> 03:10.122
How's your biking going?

03:10.206 --> 03:11.290
Oh, I don't know.

03:11.374 --> 03:12.791
My tires are inflated,
I think.

03:12.876 --> 03:14.743
Well, you know, I am not
the best cyclist,

03:14.794 --> 03:16.128
so I was gonna ride
this weekend,

03:16.212 --> 03:19.348
and I could use some tips,
if you're not busy.

03:19.415 --> 03:22.768
I...just don't know
my schedule.

03:22.852 --> 03:25.387
Yeah. Or we could just see each
other out here or at the pool sometime.

03:25.438 --> 03:27.140
But I should find out
in the next couple of days

03:27.165 --> 03:28.365
and I could call you.

03:28.641 --> 03:30.258
That'd be great.

03:30.310 --> 03:34.062
Um...I--I have a card
somewhere.

03:34.113 --> 03:35.314
Here.

03:35.381 --> 03:36.615
Um, yeah.

03:36.699 --> 03:39.568
If something changes.
It could be fun.

03:39.636 --> 03:42.871
Or at the least,
an adventure.

03:42.939 --> 03:46.375
So, uh, what made you think
I was an agent?

03:46.442 --> 03:48.160
I saw the suit.

03:48.244 --> 03:50.295
What else could you be?

03:52.799 --> 03:54.383
Bye.

03:54.450 --> 03:56.168
So, you're going, right?

03:56.252 --> 03:57.336
I don't know.

03:57.420 --> 03:58.837
Well, is she cute?

03:58.922 --> 04:00.839
Yes, she is, but I need to focus
on my training.

04:00.924 --> 04:02.341
I don't need to be
distracted.

04:02.425 --> 04:04.125
Yes, you should be
distracted.

04:04.177 --> 04:06.845
Distracted is good.
What's her name?

04:06.930 --> 04:08.463
- Beth.
- I like it.

04:08.514 --> 04:12.634
And you know what they say
about riding a bicycle.

04:12.685 --> 04:15.187
- Who's getting a bicycle?
- Nobody.

04:15.271 --> 04:16.355
Let's get started.

04:16.439 --> 04:18.574
Uh, yeah, ok. Um, so,

04:18.641 --> 04:21.944
two men were beaten
with a metal pipe

04:21.995 --> 04:23.612
in Philadelphia last night.

04:23.663 --> 04:25.814
Sam Eeks, 58, he was
in town on business.

04:25.882 --> 04:28.250
And then Bruce Thomas, 32.

04:28.317 --> 04:29.251
He worked--oh, God--

04:29.318 --> 04:31.036
he worked
at a suit shop nearby.

04:31.120 --> 04:32.320
It looks personal.

04:32.372 --> 04:35.156
There was evidence of
undoing at the crime scene.

04:35.208 --> 04:37.292
He sat them up
on crates.

04:37.343 --> 04:38.510
Demonstrating remorse.

04:38.595 --> 04:40.662
In 1976, George Geshwendt
cleaned up the crime scene

04:40.713 --> 04:42.097
and covered
all 6 victims' faces.

04:42.164 --> 04:43.382
Well, this guy
did the same thing.

04:43.466 --> 04:45.133
He even cleaned
the blood off their necks.

04:45.184 --> 04:46.718
Whichever it is,
this type of aggression,

04:46.803 --> 04:49.671
coupled with his loose grip on
reality, usually leads to more.

04:49.722 --> 04:50.907
Then we can't take
a chance that this guy's

04:50.932 --> 04:52.132
a one-hit wonder.

04:53.009 --> 04:54.843
Exactly. Which is why
we're headed to Philadelphia.

04:54.894 --> 04:56.361
Wheels up in 20.

